## Function to check skewness
def check_skew(df_skew, column, i):
    skew = stats.skew(df_skew[column])
    skewtest = stats.skewtest(df_skew[column])
    fig.suptitle('Skewness Analysis')
    #axes[i].set_title('Distribution of ' + column)
    # plt.title('Distribution of ' + column)
    sns.histplot(data=df_skew[column], kde=True, ax = axes[i])
    print("{}'s: Skew: {}, : {}".format(column, skew, skewtest))
    return

from scipy.spatial.distance import cdist
distortions = []
inertias = []
mapping1 = {}
mapping2 = {}
K = range(2,10)
silhouette = []

for k in K:
    #Building and fitting the model
    kmeanModel = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=1)
    # kmeanModel.fit(df_rfm_scaled)
    kmeanModel.fit(df_rfm_scaled_with_outliers)

    #Extract labels
    cluster_labels = kmeanModel.labels_

    distortions.append(sum(np.min(cdist(df_rfm_scaled_with_outliers, kmeanModel.cluster_centers_,"euclidean"), axis=1))/ df_rfm_scaled_with_outliers.shape[0])
    inertias.append(kmeanModel.inertia_)
    mapping1[k] = sum(np.min(cdist(df_rfm_scaled_with_outliers, kmeanModel.cluster_centers_,"euclidean"), axis=1))/df_rfm_scaled_with_outliers.shape[0]
    mapping2[k] = kmeanModel.inertia_

    #silhouette.append(silhouette_score(df_rfm_scaled_with_outliers, cluster_labels, metric='euclidean'))

# Distortion is the average of the euclidean squared distance from the centroid of the respective clusters.
# Inertia is the sum of squared distances of samples to their closest cluster centre.


fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(9, 9))
ax1.plot(K, distortions, "bx-")
ax1.set_xlabel("Values of k")
ax1.set_ylabel("Distortion")
plt.suptitle("The Elbow Method")
ax2.plot(K, inertias, "bx-")
ax2.set_xlabel("Values of k")
ax2.set_ylabel("Inertia")
plt.savefig('Elbow method.png', format='png', dpi=1000)
plt.show()

def kmeans(normalised_df_rfm, clusters_number, original_df_rfm):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters= clusters_number, random_state= 42)
    kmeans.fit(normalised_df_rfm)

    # Extract cluster labels
    cluster_labels = kmeans.labels_

    # Create a cluster label column in original dataset
    df_new = original_df_rfm.assign(Cluster = cluster_labels)

    # Initialise TSNE (T-distributed Stochastic Neighbor Embedding) -> t-SNE [1] is a tool to visualize high-dimensional data
    model = TSNE(random_state=1)
    transformed = model.fit_transform(df_new)

    # Plot t-SNE
    plt.title("Flattened graph of {} Clusters".format(clusters_number))
    sns.scatterplot(x = transformed[:,0], y = transformed[:,1], hue=cluster_labels, style= cluster_labels, palette = "Set1")

    return df_new

def snake_plot(normalised_df_rfm, df_rfm_kmeans, df_rfm_original):
    #Transform data_normalized as DataFrame and add a Cluster column
    normalised_df_rfm = pd.DataFrame(normalised_df_rfm,
                                     index=df_rfm_log_with_outliers.index,
                                     columns=df_rfm_log_with_outliers.columns)
    normalised_df_rfm['Cluster'] = df_rfm_kmeans['Cluster']

    # Melt the data into a long format so RFM values and metric names are stored in 1 column each
    df_melt = pd.melt(normalised_df_rfm.reset_index(),
                      id_vars= "Cluster",
                      #id_vars=['customer_unique_id', 'Cluster'],
                      value_vars=['recency', 'frequency', 'monetary_value', 'products'],
                      var_name='Metric',
                      value_name='Value')

    plt.xlabel('Metric')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    sns.pointplot(data=df_melt, x='Metric', y='Value', hue='Cluster')

    return

def rfm_values(df):
    df_new = df.groupby(['Cluster']).agg({
        'recency': 'mean',
        'frequency': 'mean',
        'monetary_value': 'mean',
        'products': ['mean', 'count']
    }).round(0)

    return df_new

# Using IQR score - Inter Quartile Range

sorted(df_rfm_log_with_outliers)
Q1=df_rfm_log_with_outliers.quantile(0.25)
Q3=df_rfm_log_with_outliers.quantile(0.75)
IQR=Q3-Q1
#
df_rfm_iqr = df_rfm_log_with_outliers[~((df_rfm_log_with_outliers < (Q1 - 1.5 * IQR)) |(df_rfm_log_with_outliers > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))).any(axis=1)]

def kmeans(normalised_df_rfm, clusters_number, original_df_rfm):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters= clusters_number, random_state= 42)
    kmeans.fit(normalised_df_rfm)

    # Extract cluster labels
    cluster_labels = kmeans.labels_

    # Create a cluster label column in original dataset
    df_new = original_df_rfm.assign(Cluster = cluster_labels)

    # Initialise TSNE (T-distributed Stochastic Neighbor Embedding) -> t-SNE [1] is a tool to visualize high-dimensional data
    model = TSNE(random_state=1)
    transformed = model.fit_transform(df_new)

    # Plot t-SNE
    plt.title("Flattened graph of {} Clusters".format(clusters_number))
    sns.scatterplot(x = transformed[:,0], y = transformed[:,1], hue=cluster_labels, style= cluster_labels, palette = "Set1")

    return df_new
